OL,6,F"You decide what you make of the
OL,7,Fwitnesses, you decide what you make of
OL,8,Fthe defendant and you decide what you
OL,9,Fmake of the evidence," Judge Thomas
OL,10,Ftold the jury.
OL,12,F"Emotion and sympathy must not play a
OL,13,Fpart in your decisions. You must
OL,14,Fdecide this case with your heads and
OL,15,Fnot with your hearts," he warned.
OL,17,FThe 14-year-old defendant denies three
OL,18,Fcounts of attempted murder. The case
OL,19,Fcontinues.
